Interface ModelElement

All Superinterfaces:
Adaptable, org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, Marked, Marked, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier
All Known Subinterfaces:
Base64, Block, Call, Composite, Configurator, Container, Eval, Fail, File, Filter, Interpolator, List, Map, Markdown, NamedElement, Period, Resource, Resource, Temporal, Text
All Known Implementing Classes:
Base64Impl, BlockImpl, CallImpl, CompositeImpl, ConfiguratorImpl, ContainerImpl, EvalImpl, FailImpl, FileImpl, FilterImpl, InterpolatorImpl, ListImpl, MapImpl, MarkdownImpl, ModelElementImpl, NamedElementImpl, PeriodImpl, ResourceImpl, ResourceImpl, TemporalImpl, TextImpl
public interface ModelElement extends Marked, Adaptable
A representation of the model object 'Model Element'. Base class for many Nasdanika model classes.

The following features are supported:

  • Uris
  • Description
  • Uuid
  • Action Prototype
  • Representations
  • Annotations

      org.eclipse.emf.common.util.EList<String> getUris()

    • getActionPrototype

      org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject getActionPrototype()
      Returns the value of the 'Action Prototype' containment reference. If this reference is not set then EObjectActionProvider creates a new Action using AppFactory in newAction() method. If this reference is set and is Action then a copy of the action is created and returned. Otherwise the reference value it is adapted to ActionProvider which is used to create an action. This allows to merge actions and chain action generation. E.g. generate Ecore model documentation and merge it into the Engineering documentation.
      Returns:
      the value of the 'Action Prototype' containment reference.
      See Also:
      • setActionPrototype(EObject)
      • NcorePackage.getModelElement_ActionPrototype()

    • getRepresentations

      org.eclipse.emf.common.util.EMap<String,String> getRepresentations()
      Returns the value of the 'Representations' map. The key is of type String, and the value is of type String, Mapping of representation keys to URI's of representation resources. URI's are resolved relative to the model element resource URI. During object loading resources are loaded and linked to the object. Additional processing depends on the resource type. In case of Drawio diagrams, diagram elements are semantically mapped to model elements and representation resource root elements are added as children to the object. See [Nasdanika Core Drawio](../drawio/index.html) and [Nasdanika Core EMF](../emf/index.html) documentation for more information.
      Returns:
      the value of the 'Representations' map.
      See Also:
      • NcorePackage.getModelElement_Representations()

    • getAnnotations

      org.eclipse.emf.common.util.EList<Property> getAnnotations()
      Returns the value of the 'Annotations' containment reference list. The list contents are of type Property. Annotations are used to store custom data similar to Java and Ecore annotations.
      Returns:
      the value of the 'Annotations' containment reference list.
      See Also:
      • NcorePackage.getModelElement_Annotations()
